Add three pieces of functionality to `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/transcript-reader.ts`:

## 1. New method: `readTodosFromFile(sessionId: string): Promise<TaskItem[] | null>`

Construct the todo file path and read/parse it:

```typescript
async readTodosFromFile(sessionId: string): Promise<TaskItem[] | null> {
  const todoPath = path.join(os.homedir(), '.claude', 'todos', `${sessionId}-agent-${sessionId}.json`);
  let raw: string;
  try {
    raw = await fs.readFile(todoPath, 'utf-8');
  } catch (err: unknown) {
    if ((err as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code === 'ENOENT') return null;
    throw err;
  }

  let parsed: unknown;
  try {
    parsed = JSON.parse(raw);
  } catch {
    logger.warn('[readTodosFromFile] malformed JSON in todo file', { sessionId, todoPath });
    return null;
  }

  if (!Array.isArray(parsed)) {
    logger.warn('[readTodosFromFile] expected array in todo file', { sessionId });
    return null;
  }

  let nextId = 1;
  return parsed.map((entry: Record<string, unknown>) => ({
    id: entry.id != null ? String(entry.id) : String(nextId++),
    subject: (entry.content as string) ?? '',
    status: ((entry.status as string) ?? 'pending') as TaskStatus,
    activeForm: (entry.activeForm as string) ?? undefined,
  }));
}
```

Field mapping rules:
- `content` (SDK) maps to `subject` (TaskItem)
- `status` maps directly (`pending` | `in_progress` | `completed`)
- `id` is preserved if present; generate sequential string IDs (`"1"`, `"2"`, ...) if missing
- `activeForm` maps directly (optional)

Error handling:
- `ENOENT` -> return `null` (signals fallback to JSONL)
- JSON parse error -> `logger.warn(...)`, return `null`
- Non-array JSON -> `logger.warn(...)`, return `null`
- Empty array `[]` -> return empty `TaskItem[]` (NOT null)

Import `logger` from `'../../../lib/logger.js'` (already used in other server files). Import `TaskStatus` from `@dorkos/shared/types`.

## 2. New method: `getTodoFileETag(sessionId: string): Promise<string | null>`

Return an ETag string based on file stat:

```typescript
async getTodoFileETag(sessionId: string): Promise<string | null> {
  const todoPath = path.join(os.homedir(), '.claude', 'todos', `${sessionId}-agent-${sessionId}.json`);
  try {
    const stat = await fs.stat(todoPath);
    return `"${stat.mtimeMs}-${stat.size}"`;
  } catch {
    return null;
  }
}
```

Format matches existing `getTranscriptETag()` pattern: `"${mtimeMs}-${size}"` with surrounding quotes.

## 3. Update existing method: `readTasks(vaultRoot, sessionId)`

Change `readTasks()` (currently at line 350) to try the todo file first, falling back to JSONL:

```typescript
async readTasks(vaultRoot: string, sessionId: string): Promise<TaskItem[]> {
  // Try canonical todo file first (includes subagent updates)
  const fileTasks = await this.readTodosFromFile(sessionId);
  if (fileTasks !== null) return fileTasks;

  // Fallback: reconstruct from JSONL transcript
  await validateBoundary(vaultRoot);
  const transcriptsDir = this.getTranscriptsDir(vaultRoot);
  const filePath = path.join(transcriptsDir, `${sessionId}.jsonl`);

  let content: string;
  try {
    content = await fs.readFile(filePath, 'utf-8');
  } catch {
    return [];
  }

  const lines = content.split('\n').filter((l) => l.trim());
  return parseTasks(lines);
}
```

Key behavior: When `readTodosFromFile()` returns a non-null value (including empty array), use it. Only fall back to JSONL parsing when it returns `null`.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `readTodosFromFile()` reads from `~/.claude/todos/{sessionId}-agent-{sessionId}.json`
- [ ] Field mapping: `content` -> `subject`, `status` direct, `id` preserved or sequential, `activeForm` direct
- [ ] ENOENT returns `null`, malformed JSON logs warning and returns `null`, empty array returns `[]`
- [ ] `getTodoFileETag()` returns `"${mtimeMs}-${size}"` string or `null` on ENOENT
- [ ] `readTasks()` tries file first, falls back to JSONL on `null`
- [ ] Existing `readTasks()` behavior preserved when no todo file exists
- [ ] TSDoc on all new/modified methods

Update `getSessionETag()` in `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/claude-code-runtime.ts` (line 384) to incorporate the todo file's ETag, so changes to either the transcript or the todo file invalidate the client's cache.

## Current code (line 384):

```typescript
async getSessionETag(projectDir: string, sessionId: string): Promise<string | null> {
  return this.transcriptReader.getTranscriptETag(projectDir, sessionId);
}
```

## New code:

```typescript
async getSessionETag(projectDir: string, sessionId: string): Promise<string | null> {
  const transcriptETag = await this.transcriptReader.getTranscriptETag(projectDir, sessionId);
  const todoETag = await this.transcriptReader.getTodoFileETag(sessionId);

  if (transcriptETag && todoETag) {
    // Combine both ETags so changes to either invalidate the cache
    return `"${transcriptETag.slice(1, -1)}-${todoETag.slice(1, -1)}"`;
  }
  // Return whichever is available, or null if neither exists
  return transcriptETag ?? todoETag;
}
```

The `.slice(1, -1)` strips the surrounding quotes from each individual ETag before combining them into a single quoted string. This produces a combined ETag like `"12345-1024-67890-512"` (transcript mtime-size + todo mtime-size).

Note: `getSessionTasks()` (line 379) requires NO changes -- it already delegates to `transcriptReader.readTasks()` which now handles file-first logic internally (from task 1.1).

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `getSessionETag()` calls both `getTranscriptETag()` and `getTodoFileETag()`
- [ ] When both ETags exist, combines them into a single quoted string
- [ ] When only transcript ETag exists (no todo file), returns transcript ETag alone
- [ ] When only todo ETag exists (edge case), returns todo ETag alone
- [ ] When neither exists, returns `null`
- [ ] TSDoc updated on the method

Create `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/__tests__/transcript-reader-todos.test.ts` with unit tests for the new todo file reading methods.

## Test Setup

Mock `fs/promises` for file system operations and `logger` for warning assertions:

```typescript
import { describe, it, expect, vi, beforeEach } from 'vitest';
import { TranscriptReader } from '../transcript-reader.js';
import fs from 'fs/promises';

vi.mock('fs/promises');
vi.mock('../../../lib/logger.js', () => ({
  logger: { warn: vi.fn(), debug: vi.fn(), info: vi.fn(), error: vi.fn() },
}));
vi.mock('../../../lib/boundary.js', () => ({
  validateBoundary: vi.fn(),
}));

let reader: TranscriptReader;

beforeEach(() => {
  vi.clearAllMocks();
  reader = new TranscriptReader();
});
```

## Test Cases for `readTodosFromFile()`

### 1. Valid file with multiple todos

```typescript
it('parses a well-formed todo file and maps fields correctly', async () => {
  const todos = [
    { content: 'Fix login bug', status: 'completed', id: 'fix-login-bug' },
    { content: 'Add tests', status: 'in_progress', id: '2', activeForm: 'Writing unit tests' },
    { content: 'Deploy', status: 'pending', id: '3' },
  ];
  vi.mocked(fs.readFile).mockResolvedValue(JSON.stringify(todos));

  const result = await reader.readTodosFromFile('session-123');

  expect(result).toEqual([
    { id: 'fix-login-bug', subject: 'Fix login bug', status: 'completed', activeForm: undefined },
    { id: '2', subject: 'Add tests', status: 'in_progress', activeForm: 'Writing unit tests' },
    { id: '3', subject: 'Deploy', status: 'pending', activeForm: undefined },
  ]);
  // Verify correct file path
  expect(fs.readFile).toHaveBeenCalledWith(
    expect.stringContaining('.claude/todos/session-123-agent-session-123.json'),
    'utf-8'
  );
});
```

### 2. Empty array

```typescript
it('returns empty array when file contains []', async () => {
  vi.mocked(fs.readFile).mockResolvedValue('[]');
  const result = await reader.readTodosFromFile('session-123');
  expect(result).toEqual([]);
});
```

### 3. ENOENT (file not found)

```typescript
it('returns null when file does not exist', async () => {
  const err = new Error('ENOENT') as NodeJS.ErrnoException;
  err.code = 'ENOENT';
  vi.mocked(fs.readFile).mockRejectedValue(err);
  const result = await reader.readTodosFromFile('session-123');
  expect(result).toBeNull();
});
```

### 4. Malformed JSON

```typescript
it('logs warning and returns null for malformed JSON', async () => {
  vi.mocked(fs.readFile).mockResolvedValue('not valid json{{{');
  const { logger } = await import('../../../lib/logger.js');
  const result = await reader.readTodosFromFile('session-123');
  expect(result).toBeNull();
  expect(logger.warn).toHaveBeenCalledWith(
    expect.stringContaining('malformed JSON'),
    expect.any(Object)
  );
});
```

### 5. Missing `id` field (sequential generation)

```typescript
it('generates sequential IDs when id field is missing', async () => {
  const todos = [
    { content: 'First task', status: 'pending' },
    { content: 'Second task', status: 'completed' },
  ];
  vi.mocked(fs.readFile).mockResolvedValue(JSON.stringify(todos));
  const result = await reader.readTodosFromFile('session-123');
  expect(result).toEqual([
    { id: '1', subject: 'First task', status: 'pending', activeForm: undefined },
    { id: '2', subject: 'Second task', status: 'completed', activeForm: undefined },
  ]);
});
```

### 6. Semantic slug IDs preserved

```typescript
it('preserves semantic slug IDs as-is', async () => {
  const todos = [
    { content: 'Fix the login', status: 'pending', id: 'fix-login-bug' },
    { content: 'Refactor auth', status: 'in_progress', id: 'refactor-auth-module' },
  ];
  vi.mocked(fs.readFile).mockResolvedValue(JSON.stringify(todos));
  const result = await reader.readTodosFromFile('session-123');
  expect(result![0].id).toBe('fix-login-bug');
  expect(result![1].id).toBe('refactor-auth-module');
});
```

## Test Cases for `getTodoFileETag()`

### 1. File exists

```typescript
it('returns mtime-size ETag string when file exists', async () => {
  vi.mocked(fs.stat).mockResolvedValue({
    mtimeMs: 1234567890,
    size: 512,
  } as any);
  const result = await reader.getTodoFileETag('session-123');
  expect(result).toBe('"1234567890-512"');
});
```

### 2. File missing

```typescript
it('returns null when todo file does not exist', async () => {
  vi.mocked(fs.stat).mockRejectedValue(new Error('ENOENT'));
  const result = await reader.getTodoFileETag('session-123');
  expect(result).toBeNull();
});
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] All 8 test cases pass
- [ ] Tests mock `fs/promises` (no real filesystem access)
- [ ] Tests follow existing patterns in `__tests__/` directory
- [ ] `logger.warn` assertions verify warning messages for error cases
- [ ] File path construction verified in at least one test

Add integration-level tests to `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/__tests__/transcript-reader-todos.test.ts` (same file as task 2.1) that verify the file-first fallback behavior of `readTasks()` and the ETag combination logic in `getSessionETag()`.

## readTasks() Integration Tests

These tests verify that `readTasks()` correctly prefers the todo file over JSONL parsing.

### 1. File exists -- prefer file over JSONL

```typescript
describe('readTasks() file-first fallback', () => {
  it('uses todo file when it exists, skips JSONL parsing', async () => {
    const todos = [{ content: 'Task from file', status: 'pending', id: '1' }];
    // readTodosFromFile will succeed (readFile returns valid JSON)
    vi.mocked(fs.readFile).mockResolvedValue(JSON.stringify(todos));

    const result = await reader.readTasks('/project/dir', 'session-123');

    expect(result).toEqual([
      { id: '1', subject: 'Task from file', status: 'pending', activeForm: undefined },
    ]);
    // readFile called once for todo file, NOT for JSONL transcript
    expect(fs.readFile).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);
    expect(fs.readFile).toHaveBeenCalledWith(
      expect.stringContaining('.claude/todos/'),
      'utf-8'
    );
  });
```

### 2. File missing -- fall back to JSONL

```typescript
  it('falls back to JSONL parsing when todo file is missing', async () => {
    const enoent = new Error('ENOENT') as NodeJS.ErrnoException;
    enoent.code = 'ENOENT';

    // First call (readTodosFromFile) -> ENOENT
    // Second call (readTasks JSONL fallback) -> JSONL content with TodoWrite
    vi.mocked(fs.readFile)
      .mockRejectedValueOnce(enoent)
      .mockResolvedValueOnce(
        '{"type":"assistant","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_use","name":"TodoWrite","input":{"todos":[{"content":"JSONL task","status":"pending"}]}}]}}'
      );

    const result = await reader.readTasks('/project/dir', 'session-123');

    expect(result).toEqual([
      { id: '1', subject: 'JSONL task', status: 'pending', activeForm: undefined },
    ]);
    // Both readFile calls were made: todo file (failed) + JSONL transcript
    expect(fs.readFile).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(2);
  });
});
```

Note: The JSONL fallback path calls `validateBoundary()` which is mocked (from task 2.1 setup). Also mock `fs.readdir` if needed for the transcripts directory listing, or ensure the direct file path read works.

## getSessionETag() Integration Test

This test verifies the combined ETag in `ClaudeCodeRuntime`. Create a separate test file or add to the existing `claude-code-runtime.test.ts` file at `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/__tests__/claude-code-runtime.test.ts`.

If adding to the existing runtime test file is complex due to its setup, create a focused test:

```typescript
describe('getSessionETag() with todo file', () => {
  it('combines transcript and todo ETags when both exist', async () => {
    // Mock getTranscriptETag to return a transcript ETag
    vi.spyOn(reader, 'getTranscriptETag').mockResolvedValue('"111-100"');
    // Mock getTodoFileETag to return a todo ETag
    vi.spyOn(reader, 'getTodoFileETag').mockResolvedValue('"222-200"');

    // Test via the runtime's getSessionETag which combines them
    // This requires either testing the runtime or testing the combination logic directly
  });

  it('returns only transcript ETag when todo file is missing', async () => {
    vi.spyOn(reader, 'getTranscriptETag').mockResolvedValue('"111-100"');
    vi.spyOn(reader, 'getTodoFileETag').mockResolvedValue(null);
    // Should return '"111-100"'
  });

  it('returns only todo ETag when transcript is missing', async () => {
    vi.spyOn(reader, 'getTranscriptETag').mockResolvedValue(null);
    vi.spyOn(reader, 'getTodoFileETag').mockResolvedValue('"222-200"');
    // Should return '"222-200"'
  });

  it('returns null when neither file exists', async () => {
    vi.spyOn(reader, 'getTranscriptETag').mockResolvedValue(null);
    vi.spyOn(reader, 'getTodoFileETag').mockResolvedValue(null);
    // Should return null
  });
});
```

The ETag combination test can be done at the TranscriptReader level by testing `getSessionETag()` on the runtime, or by creating a small helper test that verifies the string combination logic. Since the combination happens in `ClaudeCodeRuntime.getSessionETag()`, the cleanest approach is to spy on the TranscriptReader methods and test through the runtime.

